						<summary>

						

						<p>Another slab lying on a mound in the Sāhebu Bazaar.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1049: 1127 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1049 which may correspond to 1127 A.D. Other details of date are not given.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the grant of lands for the worship <hi rend="italic">(havibaliarchana)</hi> and food-offerings to the deity Trikōṭīśvaradēva of Vellaṁṭūra on the occasion of <hi rend="italic">Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti.</hi> It mentions the <hi rend="italic">sthānapati</hi> Īśānaśiva-paṇḍita who is endowed with a portion of the land.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. X, No. 85.</p>						

						</summary>
